<br>
I see where your mistake lies however.  The terms of &quot;country&quot; and &quot;government&quot; are synonymous within your sphere of understanding and that is a fundamental error.<br>
<br>
No one is obligated to support the government to be an American.<br>
<br>
Want to know where your notion came from, however?  It came from the Vietnam War when the media was accused of sabotaging the war effort by portraying the Vietnam campaign for what it really was.  But it was the first televeised war and the media didn't know any better and wasn't aware that the public opinion would be influenced to such a great degree by televising Vietnam.  If you notice, the U.S. media has not criticized any major American military actions ever since. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=manndrakke>Manndrakke</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/30/02 10:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mandrakke.free.fr/Manndy.gif width=150 height=190 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Keep da bombs away from mah head and I will be fine.<br>
