So fuck weakness.  Let's look at importance, and how about the damn timeline?<br>
<br>
1990 - Iraq invades Kuwait<br>
1991 - 2002 - Iraq violates UN mandates over and over again.  They break the cease fire treaty over and over again, and I'm not talking about just their military actions against our patrol planes.<br>
1995? - North Korea signs an agreement to halt their nuclear weapons program.  We appease them with needed supplies and economic help.<br>
1990s Late - North Korea test fires a long range missile that has a range greater than their distance to Japan.<br>
1998 - Iraq kicks the weapon inspectors out of their country.<br>
1998~ - It is &quot;suspected&quot; that North Korea has continued their nuclear weapons research.  (NOTHING IS DONE, the news story is hushed up.  Yippie, thanks Clinton!)<br>
2000 - Bush is elected Pres.<br>
2001 - 9-11 and war on Terror<br>
2001 - War in Afghanistan<br>
2001 Late - Pressure is applied onto Iraq, the drum begins to beat.<br>
2002 Mid - North Korea announces that have in fact been continuing their weapons research.<br>
<br>
So there you go... <br>
The way I see it, we started down the road towards Iraq BEFORE North Korea became a &quot;known&quot; problem.  Prior to this, it was only suspected, most likely heavily, but so was Iraq's situation.  So we are then left in a situation where we have TWO problems we MUST address.  Well when you being work on something, you FINISH it.  You don't pull up your stake tents and move else where.  If you did that, all the work that went into applying the pressure onto Iraq would have been wasted.  Do you think that Iraq would be this conscenting if the level of support hadn't been created?  If so, back that belief up, cause HISTORY has shown otherwise, there is no WHAT IF here.<br>
<br>
I'm fucking GLAD that Iraq has been following through, and I hope it continues and goes to a higher level.  It is known that Iraq hasn't fully followed the mandates given to them so far, that report they issued was LACKING, which is a violation.  We KNOW that they have been conducting nuclear weapons research, but the report said NOTHING about the research.  We KNOW that they have received specific materials, which were completely unaccounted for in their report.<br>
<br>
I'd rather not invade Iraq, I'd rather we just settle their crap with the inspectors.  That we find the rest of their shit, destroy it, and move on.<br>
<br>
The rethoric that is going on now about North Korea is because they are beating THEIR drum the loudest.  So what, should we just be reactionary and respond to who ever is the biggest shit at the very moment?  So we should now focus on North Korea, apply the pressure, removing the pressure from Iraq, to only have Iraq turn around and beat their drum louder?  Then switch again?<br>
<br>
NO!!  When you go to do a job, you FINISH IT! <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6094" target="top">Wenin Huirunda</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
