<br>
The simple truth as I see it, is that no matter how much Iraq complies, we will find a reason (whether real or manufactured) to go to war with them.<br>
<br>
N Korea has 500 scuds, 1.2 million troops, 11,000 artillery and God knows what else on the DMZ line (doing this from memory, but I know there was more than that). <br>
<br>
Iraq after our first war has nothing to match that and we have been beating up on them for 11 years which kep them weak. Iraq is most likely going to be like shooting fish in a barrel while N Korea will put up a helluva fight and take a hefty toll.<br>
<br>
The sad fact is that neither presents a danger to US security, only to our &quot;interests&quot;. When our interests are threatened, but not our security, then I believe negotiation is the first line of action.<br>
<br>
War is a serious thing and once commited there is no turning back. When my country goes I want to be damn sure it is for the right reasons and we have exhausted all other resonable avenues of action. If you believe we have done that with Iraq, then we disagree bigtime. I see Bush making any and every excuse to go to war with Iraq and alot of the world sees the same thing. <p><br>
